packed schedules
what a product design degree didn't teach me

alex hormozi reel

i've had many ppl come upto me to mock and question my overplanning my schedules, and i never really had a good answer to them.

the calendar schedule is who i could be in my best ideal. it sets a picture of what i have to strive towards.

but i agree where the opposing views come from, spending all this time planning isn't doint the work, its just pretending to do the work.

To which I agree. thats a rabbit hole i've fell into multiple timmes before, trying to optomize everything except just getting the work done.

however for these people focus, isnt a problem. I've realised one of the hardest things for my distracted brain to do is focus on a task and stick to it.

not having a schedule telling me what to do and when, is another hurdle that gets me distracted and loses my way.
